{{DISPLAYTITLE:''The Defector: Escape from North Korea''}}
'''''The Defector: Escape from North Korea'''''  is a 2012 [[documentary film]] about [[North Korean defectors]], directed by Korean-Canadian filmmaker [[Ann Shin]]. The film premiered at the [[Hot Docs Canadian International Documentary Festival]] and had its broadcast premiere on [[TVOntario]] on June 26. The film's release was accompanied by ''The Defector Interactive'', an [[interactive documentary]] that uses a [[videogame]]-like approach to let the user find out about life in and escape from North Korea.<ref name="current">{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/thecurrent/episode/2013/04/26/the-story-of-north-koreans-who-defect-to-china-and-beyond/|title=The story of North Koreans who defect to China and beyond|date=26 April 2013|work=[[The Current (radio program)|The Current]]|publisher=[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation]]|accessdate=27 June 2013}}</ref><ref name="Seagal">{{cite news|url=http://ca.news.yahoo.com/blogs/dailybrew/smuggler-canadian-filmmaker-team-help-n-korean-defectors-143142894.html|title=Canadian filmmaker teams up with smuggler to help North Korean defectors|last=Seagal|first=Alina|date=27 June 2013|work=[[Yahoo! News]]|accessdate=27 June 2013}}</ref><ref name="Barnard">{{cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/movies/2013/04/26/hot_docs_the_defector_tracks_a_harrowing_escape_from_north_korea.html|title=Hot Docs: The Defector tracks a harrowing escape from North Korea|last=Barnard|first=Linda|date=26 April 2013|work=[[Toronto Star]]|accessdate=27 June 2013}}</ref>

