'''Unbolted''' is a UK based online personal asset-based [[peer-to-peer lending]] platform, where individuals can borrow from other individuals by using  high value personal assets <ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.financialreporter.co.uk/specialist-lending/p2p-lender-aims-to-challenge-secured-market.html| title=P2P lender aims to challenge secured market|accessdate=2014-12-30 |work= Financial Reporter|location=London|first=Rozi|last=Jones|date=30 December 2014}}</ref> such as luxury watches, cars, fine arts, [[antiques]], [[jewellery]] and commodities such as gold. The company started trading in November 2014 and has its offices in [[London]].<ref>{{cite news | url=https://uk.finance.yahoo.com/news/unbolted-launches-challenger-brand-uk-110000499.html| title=Unbolted Launches as Challenger Brand to UK’s "Out-Dated" Pawn and Secured Lending Industry with New Peer-to-Peer Online Offering|accessdate=2014-12-30 |work= Yahoo Finance|location=London|date=30 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.crowdfundinsider.com/2014/12/60452-unbolted-peer-peer-pawn-shop/| title=Unbolted May Be the First Peer to Peer Digital Pawn Shop|accessdate=2014-12-31 |work= Crowd fund Insider|location=London|first=JD|last=Alois|date=31 December 2014}}</ref>

==History==
Unbolted was set up by Ashwin Parmeswaran and Rito Haldar with an aim to make short-term borrowing transparent, affordable and convenient for consumers and [[small business]] owners, by using their high-value personal assets to access low-cost [[loans]].<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/money/2015/jan/11/unbolted-launches-pawnbroking-wonga-era| title=‘Wonga-style’ pawnbroker set to take place of payday lenders|accessdate=2015-01-11 |work= The Guardian|location=London|first=Lisa|last=Bachelor|date=11 January 2015}}</ref> It raised [[seed funding]] in July 2014 prior to its public launch in November 2014.

